{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We’re adopting an RFC (“request for comments”) process for contributing ideas to Gatsby."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inspired by "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/reactjs/rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"React"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/yarnpkg/rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Yarn"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/emberjs/rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ember"}]},{"type":"text","value":", and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rust"}]},{"type":"text","value":", the goal is to allow Gatsby core team members and community members to collaborate on the design of new features. It’s also intended to provide a clear path for ideas to enter the project:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Create an RFC document detailing your proposal."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Submit a PR to the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RFC repository"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Incorporate feedback into the proposal."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After discussion, the core team may or may not accept the RFC."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If the RFC is accepted, the PR is merged."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RFCs are accepted when they are approved for implementation in Gatsby. A more thorough description of the process is available in the repository’s "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/rfcs/blob/master/README.md"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"README"}]},{"type":"text","value":". The exact details may be refined in the future."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"who-can-submit-rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#who-can-submit-rfcs","ariaLabel":"who can submit rfcs permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Who Can Submit RFCs?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Anyone! No knowledge of Gatsby’s internals is required, nor are you expected to implement the proposal yourself."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"what-types-of-changes-should-be-submitted-as-rfcs"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#what-types-of-changes-should-be-submitted-as-rfcs","ariaLabel":"what types of changes should be submitted as rfcs permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"What Types of Changes Should Be Submitted As RFCs?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generally, any idea that would benefit from additional review or design before being implemented is a good candidate for an RFC. As a rule of thumb, this means any proposal that adds, changes, or removes a Gatsby API."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Not every change must go through the RFC process. Bug fixes or performance improvements that don’t touch the API can be submitted directly to the main library."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"rfcs-for-a-new-github-labeling-system-and-to-remove-our-special-layout-component"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#rfcs-for-a-new-github-labeling-system-and-to-remove-our-special-layout-component","ariaLabel":"rfcs for a new github labeling system and to remove our special layout component permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"RFCs for a new GitHub labeling system and to remove our special layout component"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Coinciding with the launch of our RFC process, we’ve submitted a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/rfcs/pull/1"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"proposal for a new GitHub labeling system"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/rfcs/pull/2"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"proposal to remove our special layout component"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Both proposals have already received many valuable comments from the community that we’re incorporating into the design of the new process and API."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Both PRs are good examples of how a typical RFC should be structured. We’re excited to start receiving your proposals!"}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"excerpt":"We’re adopting an RFC (“request for comments”) process for contributing ideas to Gatsby. Inspired by  React ,  Yarn ,  Ember , and  Rust…","timeToRead":2,"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2018-04-06-introducing-gatsby-rfc-process/","publishedAt":null},"frontmatter":{"title":"Introducing the Gatsby RFC Process","excerpt":null,"date":"April 6th 2018","rawDate":"2018-04-06T00:00:00.000Z","canonicalLink":null,"tags":null,"image":null,"imageAuthor":null,"imageAuthorLink":null,"imageTitle":null,"showImageInArticle":null,"author":{"id":"Kyle Mathews","bio":"Founder @ GatsbyJS. Likes tech, reading/writing, founding things. Blogs at bricolage.io.","twitter":"@kylemathews","avatar":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='30' height='30' viewBox='0 0 30 30' version='1'%3e%3crect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f6f2f8'/%3e%3cpath d='M11 1C9 1 8 3 8 6c0 6 0 6 6 5l5-2h-4c-5 0-5-1 0-1 3-1 4 0 4 1 1 3 3 2 3-2 0-1 0-2 1-1v1l2 1c4 0 5-1 5-5V0h-9L11 1m10 19c-3 2-6 3-7 0-2-2-5 0-7 5-1 5-1 5 1 5l1-1 2-1 1 1 9 1h10v-5c0-3 0-5-1-4h-2c-3-3-6-3-7-1M1 21v5c0 4 1 4 3 3l2-2-2-1c-2-1-2-2-1-2l1-1-1-1c-1 1-1 0 0 0v-2l-2 1' fill='%23e0d6eb' fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","width":63,"height":63,"src":"/static/53e2930a00e3463fc960c3c2ff474c77/eb2ad/kyle-mathews.jpeg","srcSet":"/static/53e2930a00e3463fc960c3c2ff474c77/eb2ad/kyle-mathews.jpeg 1x,\n/static/53e2930a00e3463fc960c3c2ff474c77/2d344/kyle-mathews.jpeg 1.5x,\n/static/53e2930a00e3463fc960c3c2ff474c77/6dc12/kyle-mathews.jpeg 2x,\n/static/53e2930a00e3463fc960c3c2ff474c77/c804e/kyle-mathews.jpeg 3x"}}},"fields":{"slug":"/contributors/kyle-mathews/"}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2018-04-06-introducing-gatsby-rfc-process/","prev":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2018-04-05-gatsby-video-tutorials/","package":null,"released":true},"frontmatter":{"title":"Gatsby video tutorials a four part video series on Gatsby and Contentful by Khaled Garbaya","draft":null,"canonicalLink":"https://www.contentful.com/blog/2018/02/28/contentful-gatsby-video-tutorials/","publishedAt":"Contentful Blog","issue":null,"tags":["contentful"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2018-04-10-how-to-handle-commen